@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Statement";
}

<vc:navbar></vc:navbar>
<div class="container mt-5">
	<main role="main" class="pb-3">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-12">
				<h1 class="text-center">@Localizer["Privacy Statement"]</h1>
				<p class="text-center">
					<em>@Localizer["Last updated: May 10, 2025"]</em>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-12">
				<h2 id="introduction">@Localizer["Introduction"]</h2>
				<p>@Localizer["AnduinOS is a free and open-source Linux distribution based on Ubuntu."]<br>@Localizer["We are committed to protecting your privacy."]<br>@Localizer["This document explains how AnduinOS handles user data, clarifies its technical design regarding privacy, and outlines considerations related to upstream components."]</p>
				<hr>
				<h2 id="1-data-collection-by-anduinos">@Localizer["1. Data Collection by AnduinOS"]</h2>
				<p>
					<strong>@Localizer["AnduinOS itself does not collect, transmit, or store any user data."]</strong>
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>@Localizer["All system operations, configurations, and user activities take place locally on your own device (\"local execution\")."]</li>
					<li>@Localizer["AnduinOS does not include any telemetry, analytics, advertising, tracking, or behavior profiling mechanisms."]</li>
					<li>@Localizer["There are no hidden background processes or network communications initiated by the system for the purpose of gathering user information."]</li>
				</ul>
				<p>@Localizer["Thus, AnduinOS is fundamentally privacy-preserving by design."]</p>
				<hr>
				<h2 id="2-why-local-execution-matters">@Localizer["2. Why Local Execution Matters"]</h2>
				<p>@Localizer["Local execution means that all features and services of AnduinOS are performed"]<strong>@Localizer["entirely on your computer"]</strong>@Localizer[", without requiring communication with any external servers owned by us or third parties."]<br>@Localizer["This ensures:"]</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Control:"]</strong>@Localizer["You retain complete control over your personal data."]</li>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Transparency:"]</strong>@Localizer["No data leaves your machine without your explicit action."]</li>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Security:"]</strong>@Localizer["Reducing external communications limits exposure to interception or exploitation risks."]</li>
				</ul>
				<p>@Localizer["In a world where remote telemetry has become ubiquitous, AnduinOS deliberately minimizes external dependencies to protect users."]</p>
				<hr>
				<h2 id="3-open-source-guarantees-your-freedom">@Localizer["3. Open Source Guarantees Your Freedom"]</h2>
				<p>@Localizer["AnduinOS is distributed under the"]<a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.en.html">@Localizer["GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-v3)"]</a>@Localizer["."]<br>@Localizer["This license guarantees:"]</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Freedom to inspect:"]</strong>@Localizer["You can review the source code to verify there are no hidden tracking mechanisms."]</li>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Freedom to modify:"]</strong>@Localizer["You can adjust the code to suit your needs, including removing any components you distrust."]</li>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Freedom to redistribute:"]</strong>@Localizer["You can share AnduinOS, either modified or unmodified, under the same license terms."]</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					<strong>@Localizer["The open nature of AnduinOS empowers users to independently verify that the system respects their privacy."]</strong>
					<br>@Localizer["There are no proprietary blobs or closed modules outside of upstream dependencies explicitly inherited from Ubuntu."]</p>
				<hr>
				<h2 id="4-upstream-software-and-privacy-considerations">@Localizer["4. Upstream Software and Privacy Considerations"]</h2>
				<p>@Localizer["While AnduinOS itself does not collect any data,"]<strong>@Localizer["it integrates a wide range of upstream open-source software"]</strong>@Localizer["originating from Ubuntu, Debian, GNOME, Flathub, and other sources."]<br>@Localizer["(Some examples and references can be found"]<a href="https://gitlab.aiursoft.cn/anduin/anduinos/-/blob/1.4/OSS.md?ref_type=heads">@Localizer["here"]</a>@Localizer[")."]</p>
				<p>@Localizer["Some upstream components may have independent data collection mechanisms."]<br>@Localizer["Notably:"]</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Canonical Ltd."]</strong>@Localizer["(Ubuntu's developer) may collect certain system information for statistics and diagnostics purposes via tools like:"]<ul>
							<li>
								<code>@Localizer["ubuntu-report"]</code>
							</li>
							<li>
								<code>@Localizer["popularity-contest"]</code>
							</li>
							<li>@Localizer["Snap store background services (if Snap is manually installed by users)"]</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p>@Localizer["We strongly recommend users review Canonical's"]<a href="https://ubuntu.com/legal/data-privacy">@Localizer["Privacy Policy"]</a>@Localizer["for details."]</p>
				<p>@Localizer["AnduinOS does"]<strong>@Localizer["not"]</strong>@Localizer["modify, enhance, or introduce additional telemetry into these upstream components."]<br>@Localizer["It merely redistributes them in their original, unmodified state."]</p>
				<hr>
				<h2 id="5-how-to-handle-potential-ubuntu-telemetry">@Localizer["5. How to Handle Potential Ubuntu Telemetry"]</h2>
				<p>
					<strong>@Localizer["AnduinOS does not preinstall any telemetry-related packages"]</strong>@Localizer["such as:"]</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<code>@Localizer["popularity-contest"]</code>
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>@Localizer["ubuntu-report"]</code>
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>@Localizer["apport"]</code>
					</li>
					<li>
						<code>@Localizer["whoopsie"]</code>
					</li>
					<li>@Localizer["Snap daemon"]</li>
					<li>@Localizer["Canonical Livepatch service"]</li>
				</ul>
				<p>@Localizer["Thus, by default,"]<strong>@Localizer["AnduinOS does not participate in any system reporting, usage statistics submission, or automated crash reporting"]</strong>@Localizer["."]</p>
				<p>@Localizer["However, if you manually install packages from Ubuntu repositories or enable certain Ubuntu-specific features, some of these telemetry mechanisms may be introduced."]</p>
				<p>@Localizer["To ensure full opt-out, you can review and, if necessary, remove these packages using:"]</p>
				<pre>
					<code class="lang-bash">@Localizer["sudo apt remove popularity-contest ubuntu-report apport whoopsie"]</code>
				</pre>
				<p>
					<strong>@Localizer["Explanation:"]</strong>
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>
							<code>@Localizer["popularity-contest"]</code>
						</strong>@Localizer[": Periodically submits anonymous package usage statistics."]</li>
					<li>
						<strong>
							<code>@Localizer["ubuntu-report"]</code>
						</strong>@Localizer[": Collects basic hardware and software details at installation time."]</li>
					<li>
						<strong>
							<code>@Localizer["apport"]</code>@Localizer["&amp;"]<code>@Localizer["whoopsie"]</code>
						</strong>@Localizer[": Automated error reporting services."]</li>
				</ul>
				<blockquote>
					<p>
						<strong>@Localizer["Note:"]</strong>@Localizer["If these packages are not installed (as is the case with a clean AnduinOS installation), no action is required."]</p>
				</blockquote>
				<p>
					<strong>@Localizer["AnduinOS is committed to keeping your installation clean and telemetry-free by default."]</strong>
				</p>
				<hr>
				<h2 id="6-responsibility-clarification">@Localizer["6. Responsibility Clarification"]</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["AnduinOS is a community-driven, non-profit project"]</strong>@Localizer["maintained in spare time by volunteers."]</li>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["AnduinOS does not have a data collection infrastructure"]</strong>@Localizer["and does not share any information with governments, corporations, or any third parties."]</li>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["For privacy concerns related to third-party applications,"]</strong>@Localizer["please refer to their respective upstream privacy policies."]</li>
				</ul>
				<hr>
				<h2 id="7-contact-information">@Localizer["7. Contact Information"]</h2>
				<p>@Localizer["If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Statement or AnduinOS's privacy practices, please contact:"]</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Email:"]</strong>
						<a href="mailto:anduin@aiursoft.com">anduin@aiursoft.com</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>@Localizer["Community:"]</strong>
						<a href="https://github.com/Anduin2017/AnduinOS/discussions">@Localizer["AnduinOS GitHub Discussions"]</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</div>
